  46class Timing(ContextDecorator):
  47    def __init__(self, prefix="", on_exit=None, enabled=True):
  48        self.prefix, self.on_exit, self.enabled = prefix, on_exit, enabled
  49
  50    def __enter__(self):
  51        self.st = time.perf_counter_ns()
  52
  53    def __exit__(self, *exc):
  54        self.et = time.perf_counter_ns() - self.st
  55        if self.enabled:
  56            print(f"{self.prefix}{self.et*1e-6:6.2f} ms" + (self.on_exit(self.et) if self.on_exit else ""))

  59def colored(st, color: Optional[str], background=False):
  60    return (
  61        f"\u001b[{10*background+60*(color.upper() == color)+30+['black', 'red', 'green', 'yellow', 'blue', 'magenta', 'cyan', 'white'].index(color.lower())}m{st}\u001b[0m"
  62        if color is not None
  63        else st
  64    )  # replace the termcolor library with one line  # noqa: E501

  71class Profiling(ContextDecorator):
  72    def __init__(self, enabled=True, sort="cumtime", frac=0.2, fn=None, ts=1):
  73        self.enabled, self.sort, self.frac, self.fn, self.time_scale = enabled, sort, frac, fn, 1e3 / ts
  74
  75    def __enter__(self):
  76        self.pr = cProfile.Profile()
  77        if self.enabled:
  78            self.pr.enable()
  79
  80    def __exit__(self, *exc):
  81        if self.enabled:
  82            self.pr.disable()
  83            if self.fn:
  84                self.pr.dump_stats(self.fn)
  85            stats = pstats.Stats(self.pr).strip_dirs().sort_stats(self.sort)
  86            for fcn in stats.fcn_list[0 : int(len(stats.fcn_list) * self.frac)]:  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
  87                (_primitive_calls, num_calls, tottime, cumtime, callers) = stats.stats[fcn]  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
  88                scallers = sorted(callers.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1][2])
  89                print(
  90                    f"n:{num_calls:8d}  tm:{tottime*self.time_scale:7.2f}ms  tot:{cumtime*self.time_scale:7.2f}ms",
  91                    colored(_format_fcn(fcn), "yellow") + " " * (50 - len(_format_fcn(fcn))),
  92                    colored(f"<- {(scallers[0][1][2]/tottime)*100:3.0f}% {_format_fcn(scallers[0][0])}", "BLACK") if len(scallers) else "",
  93                )

 101def unzip2(pairs) -> Tuple[List[Any], List[Any]]:
 102    lst1, lst2 = [], []
 103    for i1, i2 in pairs:
 104        lst1 += [i1]
 105        lst2 += [i2]
 106    return lst1, lst2

 109def list_map(f: Callable, *xs: Iterable) -> List[Any]:
 110    return list(map(f, *xs))
 111
 112
 113def list_zip(*args: List[Any]) -> List[Any]:
 114    fst, *rest = args = list_map(list, args)
 115    n = len(fst)
 116    for arg in rest:
 117        assert len(arg) == n
 118    return list(zip(*args))

 121def split_half(lst: List[Any]) -> Tuple[List[Any], List[Any]]:
 122    assert not len(lst) % 2
 123    return split_list(lst, len(lst) // 2)

 126def merge_lists(which: List[bool], l1: List[Any], l2: List[Any]) -> List[Any]:
 127    l1, l2 = iter(l1), iter(l2)
 128    out = [next(l2) if b else next(l1) for b in which]
 129    assert next(l1, None) is next(l2, None) is None
 130    return out

 133def split_list(lst: List[Any], n: int) -> Tuple[List[Any], List[Any]]:
 134    assert 0 <= n <= len(lst)
 135    return lst[:n], lst[n:]

 149    assert 0 <= n <= len(lst)

 153def partition_list(bs: List[bool], l: List[Any]) -> Tuple[List[Any], List[Any]]:
 154    assert len(bs) == len(l)
 155    lists = lst1, lst2 = [], []
 156    for b, x in zip(bs, l):
 157        lists[b].append(x)
 158    return lst1, lst2

 161def lru_cache_verbose(
 162    maxsize: int = 100,
 163    typed: bool = False,
 164    tb_start: int = -12,
 165    tb_end: int = -7,
 166):
 167    def decorator(fn: Callable):
 168        @lru_cache(maxsize=maxsize, typed=typed)
 169        def wrapper(*args, **kwargs) -> Callable:
 170            return fn(*args, **kwargs)
 171
 172        def decorated_function(*args, **kwargs) -> Any:
 173            result = wrapper(*args, **kwargs)
 174            cache_info = wrapper.cache_info()
 175
 176            dblog(
 177                f"{fn.__name__}.{cache_info} {args.__hash__()}",
 178                enable=backend.LOG_LRU,
 179            )
 180            tb = "".join(traceback.format_list(traceback.extract_stack())[tb_start:tb_end]).replace("\n    ", ":\t") + "-" * 20 + "\n"
 181            dblog(f"{tb}", enable=backend.LOG_LRU)
 182
 183            return result
 184
 185        decorated_function.cache_info = wrapper.cache_info
 186        decorated_function.fn = fn
 187        return decorated_function
 188
 189    return decorator

 192def cuda_is_available():
 193    try:
 194        import subprocess
 195        import platform
 196
 197        cmd = f"nvidia-smi{'.exe' if platform.system == 'Windows' else ''}"
 198        result = subprocess.run([cmd], stdout=subprocess.PIPE)
 199        output = result.stdout.decode("utf-8")
 200        return True if "NVIDIA-SMI" in output else False
 201    except FileNotFoundError:
 202        return False

 205class Hashed:
 206    val: Any
 207
 208    def __init__(self, val):
 209        self.val = val
 210
 211    def __hash__(self) -> int:
 212        return hash((self.val,))
 213
 214    def __eq__(self, other):
 215        if isinstance(other, Hashed):
 216            if isinstance(self.val, Tensor) and isinstance(other.val, Tensor):
 217                # because Tensor.__eq__ already for Tensor.equal
 218                return id(self.val) == id(other.val)
 219            return self.val == other.val
 220        return False
 221
 222    def __repr__(self):
 223        return f"Hashed: {repr(self.val)}"

 246class dtypes:
 247    float32: Final[DType] = DType(4, 4, "float32", "f32", np.float32)
 248    uint8: Final[DType] = DType(0, 1, "uint8", "u8", np.uint8)
 249    int8: Final[DType] = DType(0, 1, "int8", "i8", np.int8)
 250    bool: Final[DType] = DType(0, 1, "bool", "i1", bool)
 251    int32: Final[DType] = DType(1, 4, "int32", "i32", np.int32)
 252    int64: Final[DType] = DType(2, 8, "int64", "i64", np.int64)
 253    uint64: Final[DType] = DType(2, 8, "uint64", "ui64", np.uint64)
 254    float16: Final[DType] = DType(0, 2, "float16", "f16", np.float16)
 255
 256    all_dtypes = (bool, float16, float32, int8, int32, int64, uint8, uint64)
 257    name_dtype_map = {k.name: k for k in all_dtypes}
 258    name_dtype_map_inv = {v: k for k, v in name_dtype_map.items()}
 259    mlir_dtype_map = {k.mlir: k for k in all_dtypes}
 260    mlir_dtype_map_inv = {v: k for k, v in mlir_dtype_map.items()}
 261
 262    @classmethod
 263    def is_int(cls, dtype):
 264        return dtype in (cls.uint8, cls.int8, cls.int32, cls.uint64, cls.int64)
 265
 266    @classmethod
 267    def is_float(cls, dtype):
 268        return dtype in (cls.float16, cls.float32)

 299class Tensor:

 312    def is_int(self) -> bool:
 313        return self.dtype in (
 314            dtypes.int8,
 315            dtypes.uint8,
 316            dtypes.uint64,
 317            dtypes.int32,

 322        return self.dtype in (dtypes.float16, dtypes.float32)

 325        return self.dtype is dtypes.uint8

 328        return self.cast(dtypes.bool)

 337        return self.cast(dtypes.int64)

 339    def half(self):
 340        return self.cast(dtypes.float16)

 342    def float(self):
 343        return self.cast(dtypes.float32)
 344
 345    def __getattr__(self, attr):
 346        if attr in vars(backend.operator_set).keys():
 347            op = getattr(backend.operator_set, attr)
 348            return partial(op, self)
 349        elif attr in vars(backend.procedure_set).keys():
 350            procedure = getattr(backend.procedure_set, attr)
 351            assert not isinstance(procedure, classmethod), f"use {attr} instead of self.{attr}"
 352            return partial(procedure, self)
 353        else:
 354            return self.__getattribute__(attr)

 371    __rmul__ = lambda self, other: self.mul(other)
 372    __div__ = lambda self, other: self.div(other)
 373    __rdiv__ = lambda self, other: self.div.func(other, self)
 374    __truediv__ = __div__
 375    __truerdiv__ = __rdiv__
 376    __pow__ = lambda self, other: self.pow(other)
 377    __rpow__ = lambda self, other: self.pow.func(other, self)
 378    __matmul__ = lambda self, other: self.matmul(other)
 379    __rmatmul__ = lambda self, other: self.matmul.func(other, self)
 380    __invert__ = lambda self: self.invert()
 381    __eq__ = lambda self, other: self.equal(other)
 382    __ne__ = lambda self, other: self.not_equal(other)
 383    __ge__ = lambda self, other: self.greater_equal(other)
 384    __le__ = lambda self, other: self.less_equal(other)

 389        return id(self.val)

 428class SymbolicTensor(Tensor):

 439    @property
 440    def val(self):
 441        raise RuntimeError(f"SymbolicTensor actually has no val, from {trace_stack[-1]=}, ")
 442
 443    @property
 444    def shape(self):
 445        return self._shape
 446
 447    @property
 448    def dtype(self):
 449        return self._dtype
 450
 451    @property
 452    def device(self):
 453        return self._device
 454
 455    def like(self, **but):
 456        shape = but.get("shape", self.shape)
 457        dtype = but.get("dtype", self.dtype)
 458        device = but.get("device", self.device)
 459        return SymbolicTensor(shape, dtype, device)
 460
 461    def str_short(self):
 462        return f'{str(self.dtype)}[{",".join(str(d) for d in self.shape)}]'
 463
 464    def __hash__(self):
 465        return hash((self.shape, self.dtype))
 466
 467    def __eq__(self, other):
 468        if type(self) != type(other):
 469            return False
 470        return tuple(self.shape) == tuple(other.shape) and self.dtype == other.dtype
 471
 472    def __repr__(self):
 473        return f"<SymbolicTensor: shape={self.shape}, dtype={self.dtype.name}, device={self.device}>"

 481class Operator:
 482    def __init__(self, name, variadic_inputs=False, nary_outputs=False):
 483        self.name = name
 484        self.variadic_inputs = variadic_inputs
 485        self.nary_outputs = nary_outputs
 486        if self.variadic_inputs:
 487            self.reorg_args = self.reorg_args_nary
 488
 489    def __hash__(self):
 490        return hash(self.name)
 491
 492    def __eq__(self, other):
 493        if not isinstance(other, Operator):
 494            return False
 495        return self.name == other.name
 496
 497    def args_fixer(self, *args, **params):
 498        return args, params
 499
 500    def __call__(self, *args, **params):
 501        args, params = self.reorg_args(args, params)
 502        args, params = self.args_fixer(*args, **params)
 503        ret = bind(self, *args, **params)
 504        if not self.nary_outputs:
 505            ret = ret[0]
 506        return ret
 507
 508    def __repr__(self) -> str:
 509        return f"<{self.name}>"
 510
 511    def typecheck(self, *args, **params):
 512        raise NotImplementedError
 513
 514    def jvp(self, *args, **params):
 515        raise NotImplementedError
 516
 517    def T(self, *args, **params):
 518        raise NotImplementedError
 519
 520    def vmap(self, *args, **params):
 521        raise NotImplementedError
 522
 523    def reorg_args(self, args, params):
 524        sig = inspect.signature(self.typecheck)
 525        args_strs = [k for k, v in sig.parameters.items() if v.kind == inspect.Parameter.POSITIONAL_OR_KEYWORD and k != "self"]
 526        params_strs = [k for k, v in sig.parameters.items() if v.kind == inspect.Parameter.KEYWORD_ONLY and k != "self"]
 527
 528        if args:
 529            if len(args) > len(args_strs):
 530                args, rest = args[: len(args_strs)], args[len(args_strs) :]
 531                if params_strs:
 532                    new_params = {k: rest_arg for k, rest_arg in zip(params_strs, rest) if k not in params}
 533                    params = {**new_params, **params}
 534            else:
 535                args = tuple([params[k] if k in params else arg for k, arg in zip(args_strs, args)])
 536                assert len(args) == len(args_strs)
 537        return args, params
 538
 539    def reorg_args_nary(self, args, params):
 540        return args, params
 541
 542    def partial_run(self, trace, tracers, **params):
 543        tracers_in = [trace.instantiate_const(t) for t in tracers]
 544        symvals_in = [t.symval for t in tracers_in]
 545        symvals_out = self.typecheck(*symvals_in, **params)
 546        tracers_out = [PartialRunTraceTensor(trace, make_unknown_pval(symval), None) for symval in symvals_out]
 547        instruction = InstructionDraft(
 548            self,
 549            tracers_in,
 550            params,
 551            symvals_out,
 552            list_map(weakref.ref, tracers_out),
 553        )
 554        for t in tracers_out:
 555            t.draft = instruction
 556        return tracers_out
 557
 558    def partial_run_instruction(self, unks_in, instruction):
 559        if any(unks_in):
 560            instruction1 = None
 561            instruction2 = Instruction(
 562                instruction.op,
 563                instruction.inputs,
 564                instruction.params,
 565                instruction.out_binders,
 566            )
 567            unks_out = [True for i in instruction.out_binders]
 568            res = [v for unk, v in zip(unks_in, instruction.inputs) if ((not unk) and type(v) is Var)]
 569        else:
 570            instruction1 = instruction
 571            instruction2 = None
 572            unks_out = [False for i in instruction.out_binders]
 573            res = None
 574
 575        return instruction1, instruction2, unks_out, res

 596class BinaryOperator(Operator):
 597    boolean_output = False
 598
 599    def args_fixer(self, x, w, **params):
 600        if isinstance(x, UndefinedPrimal) or type(w) is UndefinedPrimal:
 601            assert x.shape == w.shape
 602            return (x, w), params
 603
 604        if type(x) in TraceTensor.PYTHON_TYPES:
 605            x = backend.full(shape=(), fill_value=x, dtype=w.dtype)
 606        elif type(w) in TraceTensor.PYTHON_TYPES:
 607            w = backend.full(shape=(), fill_value=w, dtype=x.dtype)
 608
 609        shape_delta = x.ndim - w.ndim
 610        if shape_delta > 0:
 611            w = w.reshape((1,) * shape_delta + w.shape)
 612        elif shape_delta < 0:
 613            x = x.reshape((1,) * -shape_delta + x.shape)
 614
 615        shape_ret = tuple([max(x, w) for x, w in zip(x.shape, w.shape)])
 616        if x.shape != shape_ret:
 617            x = x.expand(shape_ret)
 618        if w.shape != shape_ret:
 619            w = w.expand(shape_ret)
 620
 621        if type(x) is Tensor and isinstance(w, TraceTensor):
 622            x = w._trace.pure(x)
 623        elif type(w) is Tensor and isinstance(x, TraceTensor):
 624            w = x._trace.pure(w)
 625        # TODO: https://jax.readthedocs.io/en/latest/type_promotion.html
 626        if x.dtype != w.dtype:
 627            # {int, bool} -> float
 628            if dtypes.is_float(x.dtype) ^ dtypes.is_float(w.dtype):
 629                if dtypes.is_float(w.dtype):
 630                    x = x.cast(w.dtype)
 631                elif dtypes.is_float(x.dtype):
 632                    w = w.cast(x.dtype)
 633            # bool -> int
 634            elif dtypes.is_int(x.dtype) ^ dtypes.is_int(w.dtype):
 635                if dtypes.is_int(w.dtype):
 636                    x = x.cast(w.dtype)
 637                elif dtypes.is_int(x.dtype):
 638                    w = w.cast(x.dtype)
 639            else:  # TODO: fine-grained type promotions
 640                raise NotImplementedError("No other type promotion rules")
 641
 642        return (x, w), params
 643
 644    def vmap(self, dim_size, vals_in, dims_in, **params):
 645        (x, w), (x_bdim, w_bdim) = vals_in, dims_in
 646        if x_bdim != w_bdim:
 647            if x_bdim is None:
 648                x = VMapTrace.move_vmap_dim(x, dim_size, x_bdim, w_bdim)
 649                x_bdim = w_bdim
 650            else:
 651                w = VMapTrace.move_vmap_dim(w, dim_size, w_bdim, x_bdim)
 652        return [self(x, w, **params)], [x_bdim]
 653
 654    def typecheck(self, x: SymbolicTensor, y: SymbolicTensor, **params) -> List[SymbolicTensor]:
 655        if not type(x) in (Tensor, SymbolicTensor) or not type(x) in (
 656            Tensor,
 657            SymbolicTensor,
 658        ):
 659            raise TypeError
 660        symx = SymbolicTensor.like(x, dtype=dtypes.bool if self.boolean_output else x.dtype)
 661        symy = SymbolicTensor.like(y, dtype=dtypes.bool if self.boolean_output else y.dtype)
 662        if x.dtype != y.dtype:
 663            raise TypeError(f"x.dtype ({x.dtype}) != y.dtype ({y.dtype})")
 664        if symx == symy:
 665            return [symx]
 666        shape_delta = len(symx.shape) - len(symy.shape)
 667        if shape_delta > 0:
 668            symy = symy.like(shape=(1,) * shape_delta + symy.shape)
 669        elif shape_delta < 0:
 670            x = x.reshape((1,) * -shape_delta + symx.shape)
 671            symx = symx.like(shape=(1,) * -shape_delta + symx.shape)
 672        if symx == symy:
 673            return [symx]
 674        else:
 675            shape_ret = tuple([max(x, w) for x, w in zip(symx.shape, symy.shape)])
 676            if symx.shape != shape_ret:
 677                symx = symx.like(shape=shape_ret)
 678            if symy.shape != shape_ret:
 679                symy = symx.like(shape=shape_ret)
 680            if symx != symy:
 681                raise TypeError(f"symx ({symx}) != symy ({symy})")
 682            return [symx]
 683
 684    def jvp(self, primals, tangents, **params):
 685        (x, w), (x_dot, w_dot) = primals, tangents
 686        return [self(x, w, **params)], [self(x_dot, w_dot, **params)]
 687
 688    def T(self, cotangents, x, w):
 689        (gL_y,) = cotangents
 690        if self.boolean_output:
 691            gL_y = gL_y.cast(x.dtype)
 692        if isinstance(x, UndefinedPrimal):
 693            return [gL_y, NullCotangent]
 694        elif type(w) is UndefinedPrimal:
 695            return [NullCotangent, gL_y]

 698class ReduceOperator(Operator):
 699    def args_fixer(self, x, *, dim=None, keepdim=False):
 700        if dim is None:
 701            dim = tuple(range(x.ndim))
 702        elif isinstance(dim, int):
 703            dim = (dim,)
 704        dim = tuple(a if a >= 0 else a + len(x.shape) for a in dim)
 705        return (x,), dict(dim=dim, keepdim=keepdim)
 706
 707    def vmap(self, dim_size, vals_in, dims_in, *, dim, keepdim):
 708        (x,), (x_bdim,) = vals_in, dims_in
 709        dim = tuple(a + (x_bdim <= a) for a in dim)
 710        out_bdim = x_bdim - sum(a < x_bdim for a in dim)
 711        return [self(x, dim=dim, keepdim=keepdim)], [out_bdim]
 712
 713    def typecheck(self, x: SymbolicTensor, *, dim=None, keepdim=False) -> List[SymbolicTensor]:
 714        dim = [a + len(x.shape) if a < 0 else a for a in dim]
 715        dim_ = set(dim)
 716        if keepdim:
 717            new_shape = [d if i not in dim_ else 1 for i, d in enumerate(x.shape)]
 718        else:
 719            new_shape = [d for i, d in enumerate(x.shape) if i not in dim_]
 720        return [x.like(shape=tuple(new_shape))]
 721

 723class InitOperator(Operator):
 724    def vmap(self, dim_size, vals_in, dims_in, **params):
 725        (x_bdim,) = dims_in
 726        y = self(**params)
 727        y = y.unsqueeze(x_bdim)
 728        return [y], [x_bdim]
 729
 730    def jvp(self, primals, tangents, **params):
 731        y = self(**params)
 732        y_dot = NullCotangent(y.symval)
 733        # y_dot = y.ones_like()
 734        return [y], [y_dot]
 735
 736    def T(self, cotangents, **params):
 737        return [NullCotangent(cotangents[0])]

 748class OperatorSet:
 749    def __init__(self):
 750        self.register("jit_op")(JitOp)
 751
 752    def register(self, name, variadic_inputs=False, nary_outputs=False, aliases=()):
 753        def wrap(op_cls):
 754            assert name not in vars(self)
 755            op = op_cls(name, variadic_inputs, nary_outputs)
 756            setattr(self, name, op)
 757            for a in aliases:
 758                setattr(self, a, op)
 759            return op_cls
 760
 761        return wrap

 764class ProcedureSet:
 765    def register(self, aliases=()):
 766        def wrap(f):
 767            assert f.__name__ not in vars(self)
 768            setattr(self, f.__name__, f)
 769            for a in aliases:
 770                setattr(self, a, f)
 771            return f
 772
 773        return wrap

 783class Backend:
 784    LOG_LRU = int(os.environ.get("LOG_LRU", 0))

 786    LOG_TREE = int(os.environ.get("LOG_TREE", 0))
 787    LOG_BACKEND = int(os.environ.get("LOG_BACKEND", 0))
 788    LOG_PROGRAM = int(os.environ.get("LOG_PROGRAM", 0))
 789    LOG_INIT = int(os.environ.get("LOG_INIT", 1))
 790    device_var = os.environ.get("DEFAULT_DEVICE", "cpu:0")
 791    if device_var[-2] != ":":
 792        device_var += ":0"
 793    DEFAULT_DEVICE = devices.name_idx_device_map[device_var]
 794    DEFAULT_DTYPE = dtypes.name_dtype_map[os.environ.get("DEFAULT_DTYPE", "float32")]
 795    dtype_for_indices: DType = None  # need to override

 797    def __init__(
 798        self,
 799        operator_set: OperatorSet,
 800        procedure_set: ProcedureSet,
 801    ):
 802        self.operator_set = operator_set
 803        self.procedure_set = procedure_set
 804        self.node_types = dict()
 805        self.impls = dict()
 806        self.register_node(tuple, lambda t: (None, t), lambda _, xs: tuple(xs), "tuple")
 807        self.register_node(list, lambda l: (None, l), lambda _, xs: list(xs), "list")
 808        self.register_node(
 809            dict,
 810            lambda d: list_map(tuple, unzip2(sorted(d.items()))),
 811            lambda keys, vals: dict(list_zip(keys, vals)),
 812            "dict",
 813        )
 814        self.register_node(
 815            UndefinedPrimal,
 816            lambda u: (u.symval, ()),
 817            lambda symval, _: UndefinedPrimal(symval),
 818            "UndefinedPrimal",
 819        )
 820
 821    def set_impl(self, op: Union[types.LambdaType, types.FunctionType]):
 822        def set_impl_(fn):
 823            self.impls[op] = types.MethodType(fn, self)
 824
 825        return set_impl_

 827    def register_node(self, ty: Type, to_iter: Callable, from_iter: Callable, name=None) -> None:
 828        if name is None:
 829            name = str(ty)
 830        self.node_types[ty] = NodeType(name, to_iter, from_iter)

 832    def __getattr__(self, attr):
 833        try:
 834            dblog(
 835                f"Looking {self}.{attr} in operator_set",
 836                enable=backend.LOG_BACKEND,
 837            )
 838            return getattr(self.operator_set, attr)
 839        except:
 840            pass
 841        try:
 842            dblog(
 843                f"Looking {self}.{attr} in procedure_set",
 844                enable=backend.LOG_BACKEND,
 845            )
 846            return getattr(self.procedure_set, attr)
 847        except:
 848            pass
 849        dblog(
 850            f"Fallback to default {self} getattribute",
 851            enable=backend.LOG_BACKEND,
 852        )
 853        super().__getattribute__(attr)

 855    def tensor(
 856        self,
 857        val: Union[list, tuple, np.ndarray, "TensorBuffer"] = None,
 858        dtype: Optional[Any] = None,
 859        device=None,
 860    ):

 904    @lru_cache_verbose()
 905    def jit_program(
 906        self,
 907        hashed_program: Hashed,
 908        hashed_consts: Tuple[Hashed, ...],
 909    ):
 910        program: Program = hashed_program.val
 911        typecheck_program(program)
 912        consts = [x.val for x in hashed_consts]
 913        in_symvals = [v.symval for v in program.in_binders[len(consts) :]]
 914        codegen_output: CodegenOutput = self.codegen(program, consts + in_symvals, fn_name="main")
 915        fn, code = self.compile(codegen_output)
 916        jit_output = JitOutput(program, codegen_output, fn, code, consts)
 917        return jit_output

 930    def load(self, path, single_key="_tensor"):
 931        with open(path, mode="rb") as f:
 932            with mmap.mmap(f.fileno(), length=0, access=mmap.ACCESS_READ) as m:
 933                json_len = np.int64(m[0])
 934                start = 8 + json_len
 935                metadata = json.loads(m[8:start])
 936                ret = {}
 937                for k, v in metadata.items():
 938                    if k != "__metadata__":
 939                        dtype = Tensor.mlir_dtype_map[(v["dtype"])]
 940                        data_start = start + v["data_offsets"][0]
 941                        data_end = start + v["data_offsets"][1]
 942                        t_np = np.frombuffer(m[data_start:data_end], dtype=dtype.numpy())
 943                        t = backend.tensor(t_np, dtype=dtype)
 944                        t = t.reshape(tuple(v["shape"]))
 945                        ret[k] = t
 946                if len(ret) == 1 and single_key in ret.keys():
 947                    return ret[single_key]
 948                return ret
 949
 950    def save(self, tensors: Dict[str, Tensor], path: str, single_key="_tensor"):
 951        if isinstance(tensors, Tensor):
 952            tensors = {single_key: tensors}
 953        else:
 954            assert all((isinstance(k, str) and isinstance(v, Tensor)) for k, v in tensors.items())
 955
 956        metadata, offset = {}, 0
 957        for k, v in tensors.items():
 958            metadata[k] = {
 959                "dtype": v.dtype.mlir,
 960                "shape": list(v.shape),
 961                "data_offsets": [offset, offset + v.nbytes()],
 962            }
 963            offset += v.nbytes()
 964        j = json.dumps(metadata, separators=(",", ":"))
 965        Path(path).unlink(missing_ok=True)
 966        jbytes = j.encode("utf-8")
 967        start = 8 + len(jbytes)
 968        with open(path, mode="wb") as f:  # make empty file, fill with enough space
 969            f.write(b"\x00" * (start + offset))
 970        with open(path, mode="r+b") as f:
 971            with mmap.mmap(f.fileno(), length=0, access=mmap.ACCESS_WRITE) as m:
 972                m[0:8] = np.int64(len(j)).tobytes()
 973                m[8:start] = jbytes
 974                for t, tm in zip(tensors.values(), metadata.values()):
 975                    data_start, data_end = tm["data_offsets"]
 976                    m[start + data_start : start + data_end] = t.numpy().tobytes()

1133    @classmethod
1134    def instructions_as_code(cls, program, fn_defs):
1135        def indent(code, indent_amount):
1136            spaces = " " * (len(code) - len(code.lstrip()))
1137            spaces += " " * indent_amount
1138            return "\n".join([spaces + line for line in code.strip().split("\n")])
1139
1140        in_binders_vars = [program.env[i] for i in program.in_binders]
1141        body_code_lines = []
1142        for instruction in program.instructions:
1143            if len(instruction.out_binders) == 0:
1144                continue
1145            params = instruction.params.copy()
1146            for param_name, param in params.items():
1147                if isinstance(param, Program):
1148                    sub_program = param
1149                    fn_defs = cls.instructions_as_code(sub_program, fn_defs)
1150                    program_in_vals = ", ".join(f"{program.env[x].name}" for x in instruction.inputs)
1151                    params[param_name] = f"slope.make_program({sub_program.name}, {program_in_vals})[0]"
1152                if isinstance(param, DType):
1153                    params[param_name] = f"slope.{param.name}"
1154            param_vals = ", ".join(f"{param_name}={param}" for param_name, param in params.items())
1155            in_vals = ", ".join(f"{program.env[x].name}" for x in instruction.inputs)
1156            out_vals = ", ".join(f"{program.env[z].name}" for z in instruction.out_binders)
1157            sig = program.pprint_sig(
1158                [program.env[x].symval for x in instruction.inputs],
1159                [program.env[y].symval for y in instruction.out_binders],
1160            )
1161            line = f"""{out_vals} = slope.{instruction.op.name}({in_vals}{", " if (param_vals and in_vals) else ""}{param_vals}) # {sig}"""
1162            body_code_lines += [indent(line, program.indent_amount)]
1163
1164        fn_args_str = ", ".join([f"{i.name}" for i in in_binders_vars])
1165        # fn_static_args_str = ", ".join([f"{a}={a_val}" for a, a_val in program.static_args])
1166        out_vars = [program.env[o] for o in program.outs]
1167        fn_sig = program.pprint_sig(
1168            [i.symval for i in in_binders_vars],
1169            [o.symval for o in out_vars],
1170        )
1171        head_code_line = [f"def {program.name}({fn_args_str}): # {fn_sig}"]
1172        out_str = ", ".join([f"{o.name}" for o in out_vars])
1173        tail_code_line = [indent(f"return {out_str}", program.indent_amount)]
1174        code_lines = head_code_line + body_code_lines + tail_code_line + ["\n"]
1175
1176        fn_defs[program.name] = code_lines
1177        return fn_defs

1179    @staticmethod
1180    def prune_instructions(instructions, outs):
1181        graph = dict()
1182        for instruction in instructions:
1183            parent_nodes, child_nodes = instruction.out_binders, instruction.inputs
1184            for parent in parent_nodes:
1185                if parent not in graph:
1186                    graph[parent] = set()
1187                for child in child_nodes:
1188                    graph[parent].add(child)
1189        visited_from_terminal = set()
1190
1191        def dfs(node, visited):
1192            visited.add(node)
1193            if node in graph:
1194                for neighbor in graph[node]:
1195                    if neighbor not in visited:
1196                        dfs(neighbor, visited)
1197
1198        for terminal_node in outs:
1199            dfs(terminal_node, visited_from_terminal)
1200        unreachable_nodes = set(graph.keys()) - visited_from_terminal
1201
1202        instructions_to_prune = []
1203        for instruction in instructions:
1204            parent_nodes, child_nodes = instruction.out_binders, instruction.inputs
1205            if any(node in unreachable_nodes for node in parent_nodes) or any(node in unreachable_nodes for node in child_nodes):
1206                instructions_to_prune += [instruction]
1207        new_instructions = [inst for inst in instructions if inst not in instructions_to_prune]
1208        if backend.LOG_PROGRAM:
1209            LI = len(instructions)
1210            LNI = len(new_instructions)
1211            DIFF = LI - LNI
1212            UN = len(unreachable_nodes)
1213            dblog(f"Before: {LI}\tAfter: {LNI}\tDiff vs Unreachables: {DIFF} == {UN} = {DIFF==UN}")
1214        return new_instructions

1317class JitOutput:
1318    def __init__(self, program: Program, codegen_output: CodegenOutput, fn, code: str, consts: List[Any]):
1319        super().__init__()
1320        self.program = program

1326    def __call__(self, *args, **params):
1327        args, in_tree = tree_flatten(args)
1328        args = tree_map(lambda a: a.val if isinstance(a, Tensor) else a, args)
1329        try:
1330            outs = self.fn(*args, **params)
1331            if not isinstance(outs, tuple):  # TODO: IREE FunctionInvoker destructure 1-tuple, need to undo
1332                outs = (outs,)
1333        except Exception as e:
1334            dblog(self.code, enable=backend.LOG_JIT)
1335            raise
1336        return [backend.tensor(TensorBuffer(o)) for o in outs]

1339class JitOp(MetaOperator):
1340    def meta_impl(self, *args, program: Program, **_):
1341        hashed_program = Hashed(program)
1342        num_consts = program.num_consts
1343        consts, args = args[:num_consts], args[num_consts:]
1344        hashed_consts = tuple(map(Hashed, consts))
1345        jit_output = backend.jit_program(hashed_program, hashed_consts)
1346        ret = jit_output(*consts, *args)
1347        return ret
1348
1349    def reorg_args(self, args, params):
1350        return args, params
1351
1352    def typecheck(self, *in_types, program: Program):
1353        program_type = typecheck_program(program)
1354        if not all(t1 == t2 for t1, t2 in zip(program_type.in_types, in_types)):
1355            ret = "Type mismatch program.in_types vs in_types:\n"
1356            for i, j in zip(program_type.in_types, in_types):
1357                ret += f"{i}, {j}, {i == j}"
1358            raise TypeError(ret)
1359        return program_type.out_types
1360
1361    def vmap(self, dim_size, vals_in, dims_in, program: Program):
1362        program, consts = vmap_program(program, dim_size, tuple(dims_in))
1363        outs = self(*consts, *vals_in, program=program)
1364        if not isinstance(outs, tuple):
1365            outs = (outs,)
1366        return outs, [0] * len(outs)
1367
1368    def jvp(self, primals, tangents, *, program):
1369        new_program, new_consts = jvp_program(program)
1370        outs = bind(
1371            self,
1372            *new_consts,
1373            *primals,
1374            *tangents,
1375            program=new_program,
1376        )
1377        n = len(outs) // 2
1378        primals_out, tangents_out = outs[:n], outs[n:]
1379        return primals_out, tangents_out
1380
1381    def T(self, cotangents, *invals, program):
1382        undef_primals = [isinstance(x, UndefinedPrimal) for x in invals]
1383        transposed_program, new_consts = transpose_program(program, tuple(undef_primals))
1384
1385        residuals, _ = partition_list(undef_primals, invals)
1386        outs = bind(
1387            self,
1388            *new_consts,
1389            *residuals,
1390            *cotangents,
1391            program=transposed_program,
1392        )
1393        outs = iter(outs)
1394
1395        return [next(outs) if undef else None for undef in undef_primals]
1396
1397    def partial_run(self, trace, tracers, *, program):
1398        in_unknowns = [not t.pval.is_known for t in tracers]
1399        program1, program2, out_unknowns, num_res = partial_run_program(program, in_unknowns)
1400        known_tracers, unknown_tracers = partition_list(in_unknowns, tracers)
1401        known_vals = [t.pval.const for t in known_tracers]
1402        outs1_res = bind(backend.jit_op, *known_vals, program=program1)
1403        outs1, res = split_list(outs1_res, len(program1.outs) - num_res)
1404        res_tracers = [trace.instantiate_const(full_raise(trace, x)) for x in res]
1405        outs2 = [PartialRunTraceTensor(trace, make_unknown_pval(v.symval), None) for v in program2.outs]
1406        instruction = InstructionDraft(
1407            self,
1408            res_tracers + unknown_tracers,
1409            dict(program=program2),
1410            [v.symval for v in program2.outs],
1411            list_map(weakref.ref, outs2),
1412        )
1413        for t in outs2:
1414            t.draft = instruction
1415
1416        return merge_lists(out_unknowns, outs1, outs2)
1417
1418    def partial_run_instruction(self, unks_in, instruction) -> Tuple[Instruction, Instruction, List[bool], List[Var]]:
1419        program = instruction.params["program"]
1420        program1, program2, out_unknowns, num_res = partial_run_program(program, unks_in)
1421        ins1, ins2 = partition_list(unks_in, instruction.inputs)
1422        out_binders1, out_binders2 = partition_list(out_unknowns, instruction.out_binders)
1423        res = [Var(v.symval) for v in program2.in_binders[:num_res]]
1424        instruction1 = Instruction(self, ins1, dict(program=program1), out_binders1 + res)
1425        instruction2 = Instruction(self, res + ins2, dict(program=program2), out_binders2)
1426        return instruction1, instruction2, out_unknowns, res

1553class VMapTrace(Trace):

1558        return self.main.global_data

1561        vals_in, bdims_in = unzip2((t.val, t.vmap_dim) for t in tracers)
1562        val_outs, bdim_outs = op.vmap(self.dim_size, vals_in, bdims_in, **params)
1563        return [VMapTraceTensor(self, x, bd) for x, bd in list_zip(val_outs, bdim_outs)]

1565    @staticmethod
1566    def move_vmap_dim(x, dim_size, src: int, dst: int):
1567        if src is None:  # unsqueeze and expand
1568            target_shape = list(x.shape)
1569            target_shape.insert(dst, dim_size)
1570            unsqueeze_shape = [1 if d == dst else target_shape[d] for d in range(len(target_shape))]
1571            x = x.reshape(tuple(unsqueeze_shape))
1572            x = x.expand(tuple(target_shape))
1573            return x
1574        elif src == dst:
1575            return x
1576        else:
1577            perm = [i for i in range(len(x.shape)) if i != src]
1578            perm.insert(dst, src)
1579            return x.permute(tuple(perm))

1626
1627    def new_arg(self, symval) -> ProgramTraceTensor:
1628        symval = SymbolicTensor.like(symval)
1629        tracer = self.builder.new_tracer(self, symval)
1630        self.builder.tracer_to_var[id(tracer)] = Var(symval)
1631
1632        return tracer
1633
1634    def pure(self, val: Any) -> ProgramTraceTensor:
1635        # get_or_make_const_tracer
1636        tracer = self.builder.const_tracers.get(id(val))
1637        if tracer is None:
1638            tracer = self.builder.new_tracer(self, get_symval(val))
1639            self.builder.add_const(tracer, val)
1640        # print(self.builder.const_tracers)
1641        return tracer
1642
1643    def run_op(self, op, tracers, params):
1644        symvals_in = tree_map(lambda x: x.symval, tracers)
1645        symvals_out = op.typecheck(*symvals_in, **params)
1646
1647        out_tracers = [self.builder.new_tracer(self, a) for a in symvals_out]
1648        inputs = [self.builder.getvar(t) for t in tracers]
1649        outvars = [self.builder.add_var(t) for t in out_tracers]
1650
1651        self.builder.add_instruction(Instruction(op, inputs, params, outvars))
1652        return out_tracers
1653
1654
1655class ProgramBuilder:
1656    instructions: List[Instruction]
1657    tracer_to_var: Dict[int, Var]
1658    const_tracers: Dict[int, TraceTensor]
1659    constvals: Dict[Var, Any]
1660    tracers: List[ProgramTraceTensor]
1661
1662    def __init__(self):
1663        self.instructions = []
1664        self.tracer_to_var = {}
1665        self.const_tracers = {}
1666        self.constvals = {}
1667        self.tracers = []
1668
1669    def new_tracer(self, trace: ProgramTrace, symval: SymbolicTensor) -> ProgramTraceTensor:
1670        tracer = ProgramTraceTensor(trace, symval)
1671        self.tracers += [tracer]
1672        return tracer
1673
1674    def add_instruction(self, instruction: Instruction) -> None:
1675        self.instructions += [instruction]
1676
1677    def add_var(self, tracer: ProgramTraceTensor) -> Var:
1678        assert id(tracer) not in self.tracer_to_var
1679        var = self.tracer_to_var[id(tracer)] = Var(tracer.symval)
1680        return var
1681
1682    def getvar(self, tracer: ProgramTraceTensor) -> Var:
1683        var = self.tracer_to_var.get(id(tracer))
1684        assert var is not None
1685        return var
1686
1687    def add_const(self, tracer: ProgramTraceTensor, val: Any) -> Var:
1688        var = self.add_var(tracer)
1689        self.const_tracers[id(val)] = tracer
1690        self.constvals[var] = val
1691        return var
1692
1693    def build(self, in_tracers: Any, out_tracers: Any, static_args, name) -> Tuple[Program, List[Any]]:
1694        constvars, constvals = unzip2(self.constvals.items())
1695        t2v = lambda t: self.tracer_to_var[id(t)]
1696        in_binders = constvars + [t2v(t) for t in in_tracers]
1697        out_vars = [t2v(t) for t in out_tracers]
1698        program = Program(
1699            in_binders,
1700            self.instructions,
1701            out_vars,
1702            len(constvals),
1703            static_args,
1704            name,
1705        )
1706        typecheck_program(program)
1707        program, constvals = self._inline_literals(program, constvals)
1708        typecheck_program(program)
1709        # dblog(program, enable=backend.LOG_PROGRAM)
1710        return program, constvals
1711
1712    def _inline_literals(self, program: Program, consts: List[Any]) -> Tuple[Program, List[Any]]:
1713        const_binders, other_binders = split_list(program.in_binders, len(consts))
1714        scalars = [type(x) in TraceTensor.PYTHON_TYPES and not get_symval(x).shape for x in consts]
1715        new_const_binders, lit_binders = partition_list(scalars, const_binders)
1716        new_consts, lit_vals = partition_list(scalars, consts)
1717        literals = dict(list_zip(lit_binders, list_map(Lit, lit_vals)))
1718        new_outs = [literals.get(x, x) for x in program.outs]
1719        new_instructions = [
1720            Instruction(
1721                instruction.op,
1722                [literals.get(x, x) for x in instruction.inputs],
1723                instruction.params,
1724                instruction.out_binders,
1725            )
1726            for instruction in program.instructions
1727        ]
1728        new_program = Program(
1729            new_const_binders + other_binders,
1730            new_instructions,
1731            new_outs,
1732            len(new_consts),
1733            program.static_args,
1734            program.name,
1735        )
1736        return new_program, tuple(new_consts)

1809class PartialRunTraceTensor(TraceTensor):
1810    def __init__(self, trace, pval, draft):
1811        self._trace = trace
1812        self.pval = pval
1813        self.draft = draft
1814
1815    symval = property(lambda self: self.pval.symval)
1816    val = property(lambda self: self.pval.const)
1817
1818    def full_lower(self):
1819        if self.pval.is_known:
1820            return full_lower(self.pval.const)
1821        return self

1824class PartialRunTrace(Trace):
1825    def new_arg(self, pval: PartialValue) -> Any:
1826        return PartialRunTraceTensor(self, pval, LambdaBindingDraft())
1827
1828    def pure(self, val: Any) -> PartialRunTraceTensor:
1829        return PartialRunTraceTensor(self, make_known_pval(val), None)
1830
1831    def instantiate_const(self, tracer: PartialRunTraceTensor) -> PartialRunTraceTensor:
1832        if tracer.pval.is_unknown:
1833            return tracer
1834        else:
1835            pval = make_unknown_pval(SymbolicTensor.like(tracer.symval))
1836            return PartialRunTraceTensor(self, pval, ConstDraft(tracer.pval.const))
1837
1838    def run_op(self, op, tracers, params):
1839        is_knowns = tuple(t.pval.is_known for t in tracers)
1840
1841        if all(is_knowns):
1842            return bind(op, *list_map(full_lower, tracers), **params)
1843        return op.partial_run(self, tracers, **params)

1882def get_symval(x):

1884        return x.symval
1885    elif type(x) in TraceTensor.PYTHON_TYPES:

1895def tree_flatten(x: Any) -> Any:
1896    def _tree_flatten(x_: Any) -> Tuple[Iterable, Union[TreeDef, Leaf]]:
1897        node_type = None
1898        for k in backend.node_types.keys():
1899            if isinstance(x_, k):
1900                node_type = backend.node_types[k]
1901
1902        if node_type is not None:
1903            node_metadata, children = node_type.flatten(x_)
1904            children_flat, child_trees = unzip2(list_map(_tree_flatten, children))
1905            children_iter = itertools.chain.from_iterable(children_flat)
1906            treedef = TreeDef(node_type, node_metadata, tuple(child_trees))
1907            return children_iter, treedef
1908        else:
1909            return (x_,), Leaf(x_)
1910
1911    children_iter, treedef = _tree_flatten(x)
1912    return tuple(children_iter), treedef

1915def tree_unflatten(treedef: TreeDef, xs: Tuple[Any]) -> Any:
1916    def _tree_unflatten(treedef_: TreeDef, xs_: Iterator) -> Any:
1917        if isinstance(treedef_, Leaf):
1918            dblog(f"    tree leaf found: {xs_}\n", enable=backend.LOG_TREE)
1919            return next(xs_)
1920        else:
1921            dblog(f"    now\n  {treedef_}", enable=backend.LOG_TREE)
1922            children = (_tree_unflatten(t, xs_) for t in treedef_.child_treedefs)
1923            dblog(f"{children=}\n", enable=backend.LOG_TREE)
1924            return treedef_.node_type.unflatten(treedef_.node_metadata, children)
1925
1926    dblog(f"unflattening {treedef}", enable=backend.LOG_TREE)
1927    return _tree_unflatten(treedef, iter(xs))
1928    # with Timing(f"\nTREE:\n{treedef}"):
1929    #     ret = _tree_unflatten(treedef, iter(xs))
1930    # return ret

1933def tree_transpose(
1934    outer_treedef: TreeDef,
1935    inner_treedef: TreeDef,
1936    tree_to_transpose: Any,
1937) -> Any:
1938    flat, treedef = tree_flatten(tree_to_transpose)
1939    inner_size = inner_treedef.num_leaves
1940    outer_size = outer_treedef.num_leaves
1941    if treedef.num_leaves != (inner_size * outer_size):
1942        raise TypeError
1943    iter_flat = iter(flat)
1944    lol = [[next(iter_flat) for _ in range(inner_size)] for __ in range(outer_size)]
1945    permuted_lol = zip(*lol)
1946    subtrees = map(partial(tree_unflatten, outer_treedef), permuted_lol)
1947    return tree_unflatten(inner_treedef, subtrees)

1950def flatten_fn(f, in_tree, *, has_aux=False):
1951    store = Store()
1952
1953    def flat_fn(*args_flat, **params):
1954        tree_args = tree_unflatten(in_tree, args_flat)
1955        out = f(*tree_args, **params)
1956        if has_aux:
1957            out, aux = out
1958        out_flat, out_tree = tree_flatten(out)
1959        store.set_value(out_tree)
1960        return (out_flat, aux) if has_aux else out_flat
1961
1962    return flat_fn, store

1965def tree_map(f: Callable[..., Any], tree, *rest, out_leaf=False) -> Any:
1966    leaves, treedef = tree_flatten(tree)
1967    if len(rest) == 0:
1968        out_tree_flat = tuple(f(leaf) for leaf in leaves)
1969        out_tree = tree_unflatten(treedef, out_tree_flat)
1970    else:
1971        all_leaves = [leaves]
1972        for t in rest:
1973            t_leaves, t_treedef = tree_flatten(t)
1974            assert t_treedef == treedef
1975            all_leaves += [t_leaves]
1976
1977        out_tree_flat = tuple(f(*xs) for xs in zip(*all_leaves))
1978        out_tree = tree_unflatten(treedef, out_tree_flat)
1979    ret = out_tree
1980    if out_leaf:
1981        ret = (ret, tree_flatten(out_tree_flat[0]))
1982    return ret

1998def bind(op, *args, **params):
1999    top_trace = find_top_trace(args)
2000    tracers = tuple([full_raise(top_trace, arg) for arg in args])
2001    outs = top_trace.run_op(op, tracers, params)
2002    lowered = tuple([full_lower(out) for out in outs])
2003    return lowered

2006def find_top_trace(xs) -> Trace:
2007    arrs = []
2008
2009    def get_arr_from_seq(seq):
2010        nonlocal arrs
2011        for x in seq:
2012            if type(x) in (tuple, list):
2013                get_arr_from_seq(x)
2014            elif isinstance(x, TraceTensor):
2015                arrs += [x]
2016
2017    get_arr_from_seq(xs)
2018    arrs = tuple(arrs)
2019    top_main = max(
2020        (x._trace.main for x in arrs),
2021        default=trace_stack[0],
2022        key=operator_py.attrgetter("level"),
2023    )
2024    if stashed_trace and stashed_trace.level > top_main.level:
2025        top_main = stashed_trace
2026    return top_main.trace_type(top_main)

2029def full_raise(trace: Trace, val: Any) -> TraceTensor:
2030    if not isinstance(val, TraceTensor):
2031        return trace.pure(val)
2032    level = trace.main.level
2033    if val._trace.main is trace.main:
2034        return val
2035    elif val._trace.main.level < level:
2036        return trace.pure(val)
2037    elif val._trace.main.level > level:
2038        raise Exception(f"Can't lift level {val._trace.main.level} to {level}.")
2039    else:
2040        raise Exception(f"Different traces at same level: {val._trace}, {trace}.")

2043def full_lower(val: Any):
2044    if isinstance(val, TraceTensor):
2045        return val.full_lower()
2046    elif type(val) in (list, tuple):
2047        return tuple(full_lower(v) for v in val)
2048    else:
2049        return val

2052def typecheck_program(program: Program) -> ProgramType:
2053    env: Set[Var] = set()
2054
2055    for v in program.in_binders:
2056        if v in env:
2057            raise TypeError
2058        env.add(v)
2059
2060    for instruction in program.instructions:
2061        in_types = [typecheck_atom(env, x) for x in instruction.inputs]
2062        out_types = instruction.op.typecheck(*in_types, **instruction.params)
2063        for out_binder, out_type in list_zip(instruction.out_binders, out_types):
2064            if not out_type == out_binder.symval:
2065                raise TypeError
2066        for out_binder in instruction.out_binders:
2067            if out_binder in env:
2068                raise TypeError
2069            env.add(out_binder)
2070
2071    in_types = [v.symval for v in program.in_binders]
2072    out_types = [typecheck_atom(env, x) for x in program.outs]
2073    return ProgramType(tuple(in_types), tuple(out_types))

2076def typecheck_atom(env: Set[Var], x: Atom) -> SymbolicTensor:
2077    if isinstance(x, Var):
2078        if x not in env:
2079            raise TypeError("unbound variable")
2080        return x.symval
2081    elif isinstance(x, Lit):
2082        return get_symval(x.val)
2083    else:
2084        assert False

2087def run_program(program: Program, args: List[Any]) -> List[Any]:
2088    env: Dict[Var, Any] = {}
2089
2090    def read(x: Atom) -> Any:
2091        return env[x] if type(x) is Var else x.val
2092
2093    def write(v: Var, val: Any) -> None:
2094        assert v not in env  # single-assignment
2095        env[v] = val
2096
2097    list_map(write, program.in_binders, args)
2098    for instruction in program.instructions:
2099        in_vals = list_map(read, instruction.inputs)
2100        outs = bind(instruction.op, *in_vals, **instruction.params)
2101        list_map(write, instruction.out_binders, outs)
2102    return list_map(read, program.outs)

2105def program_as_fun(program: Program):
2106    return lambda *args: run_program(program, args)

2109def vmap_flat(f, in_dim, out_dim, dim_size, *args):
2110    if dim_size is None:
2111        dims = set([x.shape[d] for x, d in list_zip(args, in_dim) if d is not None])
2112        assert len(dims) == 1
2113        (dim_size,) = dims
2114    with new_main_trace(VMapTrace, dim_size) as main:
2115        trace = VMapTrace(main)
2116        tracers_in = [VMapTraceTensor(trace, x, dim) if dim is not None else x for x, dim in list_zip(args, in_dim)]
2117        outs = f(*tracers_in)
2118        tracers_out = [full_raise(trace, out) for out in outs]
2119        vals_out, y_vmap_dims = unzip2((t.val, t.vmap_dim) for t in tracers_out)
2120    ret = [VMapTrace.move_vmap_dim(val_out, dim_size, bdim, out_dim) for val_out, bdim, out_dim in zip(vals_out, y_vmap_dims, out_dim)]
2121    return ret

2124def vmap(f, in_dim=0, out_dim=0, dim_size=None):
2125    def batched_f(*args):
2126        nonlocal in_dim, out_dim, dim_size
2127        args_flat, in_tree = tree_flatten(args)
2128        in_dim = (in_dim,) * len(args) if isinstance(in_dim, int) else in_dim
2129        out_dim = (out_dim,) * len(args) if isinstance(out_dim, int) else out_dim
2130        in_dim_flat, in_dim_tree = tree_flatten(in_dim)
2131        out_dim_flat, out_dim_tree = tree_flatten(out_dim)
2132        if not (in_tree == in_dim_tree == out_dim_tree):
2133            raise TypeError(f"\n{in_tree}\n!=\n{in_dim_tree}!=\n{out_dim_tree}")
2134        f_flat, out_tree_store = flatten_fn(f, in_tree)
2135        # if len(args_flat) > len(in_dim_flat):
2136        #     in_dim_flat = (in_dim[0],) * len(args_flat)
2137        outs_flat = vmap_flat(f_flat, in_dim_flat, out_dim_flat, dim_size, *args_flat)
2138        return tree_unflatten(out_tree_store(), outs_flat)
2139
2140    return batched_f

2143def jvp_flat(f, primals, tangents, *, has_aux, global_data, **static_args):
2144    with new_main_trace(JVPTrace, global_data) as main:

2146        tracers_in = [JVPTraceTensor(trace, x, t) for x, t in list_zip(primals, tangents)]

2150            # aux_ = aux
2151            aux = tree_map(lambda x: x.primal, aux)
2152            # aux = tree_map(lambda x: x.full_lower(), aux)
2153            #
2154        else:
2155            outs = jvp_flat_ret
2156        tracers_out = [full_raise(trace, out) for out in outs]
2157        primals_out, tangents_out = unzip2((t.primal, t.tangent) for t in tracers_out)

2161def jvp(f, primals, tangents, *, has_aux=False, global_data=None, **static_args):
2162    primals_flat, in_tree = tree_flatten(primals)
2163    tangents_flat, in_tree2 = tree_flatten(tangents)
2164    for p, t in zip(primals_flat, tangents_flat):
2165        assert p.shape == t.shape, f"{p.shape=} != {t.shape=}"
2166        assert p.dtype == t.dtype, f"{p.dtype=} != {t.dtype=}"
2167        assert p.device == t.device, f"{p.device=} != {t.device=}"
2168    if in_tree != in_tree2:
2169        raise TypeError
2170    f, out_tree_store = flatten_fn(f, in_tree, has_aux=has_aux)
2171    jvp_ret = jvp_flat(
2172        f,
2173        primals_flat,
2174        tangents_flat,
2175        has_aux=has_aux,
2176        global_data=global_data,
2177        **static_args,
2178    )
2179    if has_aux:
2180        (primals_out_flat, tangents_out_flat), aux = jvp_ret
2181    else:
2182        (primals_out_flat, tangents_out_flat) = jvp_ret
2183    primals_out = tree_unflatten(out_tree_store(), primals_out_flat)
2184    tangents_out = tree_unflatten(out_tree_store(), tangents_out_flat)
2185    return ((primals_out, tangents_out), aux) if has_aux else (primals_out, tangents_out)

2292def partial_run_program(
2293    program: Program,
2294    in_unknowns: List[bool],
2295    instantiate: Optional[List[bool]] = None,
2296) -> Tuple[Program, Program, List[bool], int]:
2297    env: Dict[Var, bool] = {}
2298    residuals: Set[Var] = set()
2299
2300    def read(x: Atom) -> bool:
2301        return type(x) is Var and env[x]
2302
2303    def write(unk: bool, v: Var) -> None:
2304        env[v] = unk
2305
2306    instructions1, instructions2 = [], []
2307    list_map(write, in_unknowns, program.in_binders)
2308
2309    for instruction in program.instructions:
2310        unks_in = list_map(read, instruction.inputs)
2311        (
2312            instruction1,
2313            instruction2,
2314            unks_out,
2315            res,
2316        ) = instruction.op.partial_run_instruction(unks_in, instruction)
2317        if instruction1 is not None:
2318            instructions1 += [instruction1]
2319        if instruction2 is not None:
2320            instructions2 += [instruction2]
2321        if res is not None:
2322            residuals.update(res)
2323        list_map(write, unks_out, instruction.out_binders)
2324
2325    out_unknowns = list_map(read, program.outs)
2326    if instantiate is not None:
2327        for v, uk, inst in zip(program.outs, out_unknowns, instantiate):
2328            if inst and not uk:
2329                if type(v) is Var:
2330                    residuals.add(v)
2331        out_unknowns = list_map(operator_py.or_, out_unknowns, instantiate)
2332
2333    residuals, num_res = list(residuals), len(residuals)
2334    assert all(type(v) is Var for v in residuals), residuals
2335
2336    ins1, ins2 = partition_list(in_unknowns, program.in_binders)
2337    outs1, outs2 = partition_list(out_unknowns, program.outs)
2338
2339    program1 = Program(
2340        ins1,
2341        instructions1,
2342        outs1 + residuals,
2343        0,
2344        program.static_args,
2345        f"{program.name}_partial1",
2346    )
2347    program2 = Program(
2348        residuals + ins2,
2349        instructions2,
2350        outs2,
2351        0,
2352        program.static_args,
2353        f"{program.name}_partial2",
2354    )
2355    typecheck_partial_run_program(program, in_unknowns, out_unknowns, program1, program2)
2356
2357    return program1, program2, out_unknowns, num_res

2360def typecheck_partial_run_program(program, in_unknowns, out_unknowns, program1, program2):
2361    programty = typecheck_program(program)  # (a1,  a2) -> (b1, b2 )
2362    program1ty = typecheck_program(program1)  #  a1       -> (b1, res)
2363    program2ty = typecheck_program(program2)  # (res, a2) -> b2
2364
2365    a1, a2 = partition_list(in_unknowns, programty.in_types)
2366    b1, b2 = partition_list(out_unknowns, programty.out_types)
2367    b1_, res = split_list(program1ty.out_types, len(b1))
2368    res_, a2_ = split_list(program2ty.in_types, len(res))
2369    b2_ = program2ty.out_types
2370
2371    a1 = tuple(a1)
2372    a2, a2_ = tuple(a2), tuple(a2_)
2373    b1, b1_ = tuple(b1), tuple(b1_)
2374    b2, b2_ = tuple(b2), tuple(b2_)
2375    res, res_ = tuple(res), tuple(res_)
2376
2377    if program1ty.in_types != a1:
2378        raise TypeError
2379    if program2ty.out_types != b2:
2380        raise TypeError
2381    if b1 != b1_:
2382        raise TypeError
2383    if res != res_:
2384        raise TypeError
2385    if a2 != a2_:
2386        raise TypeError
2387    if b2 != b2_:
2388        raise TypeError

2392    pvals_in = [make_known_pval(x) for x in primals_in] + [make_unknown_pval(SymbolicTensor.like(get_symval(x))) for x in primals_in]
2393
2394    def f_jvp(*primals_tangents_in):

2396        if has_aux:
2397            (primals_out, tangents_out), aux = jvp_ret
2398            return ((*primals_out, *tangents_out), aux)

2400            primals_out, tangents_out = jvp_ret

2436def tracers_to_program(
2437    tracers_in: List["PartialRunTraceTensor"],
2438    tracers_out: List["PartialRunTraceTensor"],
2439):
2440    def tracer_parents(t: PartialRunTraceTensor) -> List[PartialRunTraceTensor]:
2441        return t.draft.tracers_in if isinstance(t.draft, InstructionDraft) else []
2442
2443    def draft_to_instruction(tracer_to_var: Dict[int, Var], draft: InstructionDraft) -> Instruction:
2444        inputs = [tracer_to_var[id(t)] for t in draft.tracers_in]
2445        out_binders = [Var(symval) for symval in draft.symvals_out]
2446        for t_ref, var in list_zip(draft.tracer_refs_out, out_binders):
2447            if t_ref() is not None:
2448                tracer_to_var[id(t_ref())] = var
2449        return Instruction(draft.prim, inputs, draft.params, out_binders)
2450
2451    tracer_to_var: Dict[int, Var] = {id(t): Var(SymbolicTensor.like(t.symval)) for t in tracers_in}
2452    constvar_to_val: Dict[int, Any] = {}
2453    constid_to_var: Dict[int, Var] = {}
2454    processed_instructions: Set[int] = set()
2455    instructions: List[Instruction] = []
2456    for t in toposort(tracers_out, tracer_parents):
2457        if isinstance(t.draft, LambdaBindingDraft):
2458            assert id(t) in set(list_map(id, tracers_in))
2459        elif isinstance(t.draft, ConstDraft):
2460            val = t.draft.val
2461            var = constid_to_var.get(id(val))
2462            if var is None:
2463                symval = SymbolicTensor.like(get_symval(val))
2464                var = constid_to_var[id(val)] = Var(symval)
2465                constvar_to_val[var] = val
2466            tracer_to_var[id(t)] = var
2467        elif isinstance(t.draft, InstructionDraft):
2468            if id(t.draft) not in processed_instructions:
2469                instructions += [draft_to_instruction(tracer_to_var, t.draft)]
2470                processed_instructions.add(id(t.draft))
2471        else:
2472            raise TypeError(t.draft)
2473
2474    constvars, constvals = unzip2(constvar_to_val.items())
2475    in_binders = constvars + [tracer_to_var[id(t)] for t in tracers_in]
2476    # out_vars = [tracer_to_var[id(t)] for t in tracers_out if id(t) in tracer_to_var]
2477    out_vars = [tracer_to_var[id(t)] for t in tracers_out]
2478    program = Program(tuple(in_binders), tuple(instructions), tuple(out_vars))
2479    typecheck_program(program)
2480    return program, constvals

2483def toposort(out_nodes: List[Any], parents: Callable[[Any], List[Any]]):
2484    def check_toposort(nodes: List[Any], parents: Callable[[Any], List[Any]]):
2485        seen = set()
2486        for node in nodes:
2487            assert all(id(parent) in seen for parent in parents(node))
2488            seen.add(id(node))
2489
2490    def remove_duplicates(lst):
2491        seen = set()
2492        return [x for x in lst if id(x) not in seen and not seen.add(id(x))]
2493
2494    if not out_nodes:
2495        return []
2496    out_nodes = remove_duplicates(out_nodes)
2497
2498    child_counts = {}
2499    stack = list(out_nodes)
2500    while stack:
2501        node = stack.pop()
2502        if id(node) in child_counts:
2503            child_counts[id(node)] += 1
2504        else:
2505            child_counts[id(node)] = 1
2506            stack.extend(parents(node))
2507    for node in out_nodes:
2508        child_counts[id(node)] -= 1
2509
2510    sorted_nodes = []
2511    childless_nodes = [node for node in out_nodes if not child_counts[id(node)]]
2512    while childless_nodes:
2513        node = childless_nodes.pop()
2514        sorted_nodes += [node]
2515        for parent in parents(node):
2516            if child_counts[id(parent)] == 1:
2517                childless_nodes += [parent]
2518            else:
2519                child_counts[id(parent)] -= 1
2520
2521    sorted_nodes = sorted_nodes[::-1]
2522    check_toposort(sorted_nodes, parents)
2523    return sorted_nodes

2590def backward_pass(program: Program, args: List[Any], cotangents: List[Any]) -> List[Any]:
2591    primal_env: Dict[Var, Any] = {}
2592    ct_env: Dict[Var, Any] = {}
2593
2594    def read_primal(x: Atom) -> Any:
2595        return primal_env.get(x, UndefinedPrimal(x.symval)) if type(x) is Var else x.val
2596
2597    def write_primal(v: Var, val: Any) -> None:
2598        if type(val) is not UndefinedPrimal:
2599            primal_env[v] = val
2600
2601    def read_cotangent(v: Var) -> Any:
2602        return ct_env.pop(v, backend.zeros(v.symval.shape, v.symval.dtype))
2603
2604    def write_cotangent(x: Atom, ct: Any):
2605        if type(x) is Var and ct is not NullCotangent:
2606            ct_env[x] = (ct_env[x] + ct) if x in ct_env else ct
2607
2608    list_map(write_primal, program.in_binders, args)
2609    list_map(write_cotangent, program.outs, cotangents)
2610    for instruction in program.instructions[::-1]:
2611        primals_in = list_map(read_primal, instruction.inputs)
2612        cotangents_in = list_map(read_cotangent, instruction.out_binders)
2613        inp, params = primals_in, instruction.params
2614        cotangents_out = instruction.op.T(cotangents_in, *inp, **params)
2615        list_map(write_cotangent, instruction.inputs, cotangents_out)
2616
2617    ret = [read_cotangent(v) for v, x in list_zip(program.in_binders, args) if isinstance(x, UndefinedPrimal)]
2618    return ret

2639def grad(f, argnums=(0,), argnames="", has_aux=False, return_value=False):
2640    f, rejit = (f, False) if not isinstance(f, jit) else (f.f, True)
2641    if isinstance(argnums, int):
2642        argnums = (argnums,)
2643
2644    def gfn(x, *xs, **static_args):
2645        vjp_ret = vjp(f, x, *xs, has_aux=has_aux, **static_args)
2646        if has_aux:
2647            y, f_vjp, aux = vjp_ret
2648        else:
2649            y, f_vjp = vjp_ret
2650        if np.shape(y) != ():
2651            raise TypeError("grad output must be 0-dim scalar with shape ()")
2652        gL_xs = f_vjp(backend.ones(()))
2653        gL_xs = tuple(gL_xs[i] for i in argnums) if len(argnums) > 1 else gL_xs[argnums[0]]
2654        if return_value:
2655            return ((y, aux), gL_xs) if has_aux else (y, gL_xs)
2656        else:
2657            return (gL_xs, aux) if has_aux else gL_xs
2658
2659    return jit(gfn) if rejit else gfn

2672def jit_partial_run(trace, tracers, *, program):
2673    in_unknowns = [not t.pval.is_known for t in tracers]
2674    program1, program2, out_unknowns, num_res = partial_run_program(program, in_unknowns)
2675    known_tracers, unknown_tracers = partition_list(in_unknowns, tracers)
2676    known_vals = [t.pval.const for t in known_tracers]
2677    outs1_res = backend.jit_op(*known_vals, program=program)
2678    outs1, res = split_list(outs1_res, len(program1.outs) - num_res)
2679    res_tracers = [trace.instantiate_const(full_raise(trace, x)) for x in res]
2680    outs2 = [PartialRunTraceTensor(trace, PartialValue.unknown(v.symval), None) for v in program2.outs]
2681    draft = InstructionDraft(
2682        backend.jit_op,
2683        res_tracers + unknown_tracers,
2684        dict(program=program2),
2685        [v.symval for v in program2.outs],
2686        map(weakref.ref, outs2),
2687    )
2688    for t in outs2:
2689        t.draft = draft
2690    return merge_lists(out_unknowns, outs1, outs2)

2707    @classmethod
2708    def get_jit_name(cls, args, static_args, prefix="jit", short=False):
2709        name = f"{prefix}_"
2710        if short:
2711            static_args_tup = tuple(static_args.items())
2712            ids = repr(hash((prefix, args, static_args_tup)))[-4:]
2713            name = f"{prefix}_{ids}"
2714        else:
2715            for a in args:
2716                name += f"shape_{a.shape}_dtype_{a.dtype.name}_"
2717            for k, v in static_args.items():
2718                name += f"{k}_{v}_"
2719            name = name.replace("(", "_lp_")
2720            name = name.replace(")", "_rp_")
2721            name = name.replace(",", "_cm_")
2722            name = name.replace(" ", "")
2723            name = name.replace(".", "_dt_")
2724
2725        return name

2727    def get_program(self, *args, **static_args):
2728        sig = inspect.signature(self.f)
2729        if all("*" not in repr(v) for v in sig.parameters.values()):
2730            args_strs = [k for k, v in sig.parameters.items() if k != "self" and k not in self.static_argnames]
2731            static_args_strs = [k for k, v in sig.parameters.items() if k != "self" and k in self.static_argnames]
2732
2733            if args:
2734                if len(args) > len(args_strs):
2735                    assert static_args_strs
2736                    args, rest = args[: len(args_strs)], args[len(args_strs) :]
2737                    new_static_args = {k: rest_arg for k, rest_arg in zip(static_args_strs, rest) if k not in static_args}
2738                    static_args = {**new_static_args, **static_args}
2739            else:
2740                args = tuple([static_args[k] if k in static_args else arg for k, arg in zip(args_strs, args)])
2741
2742        symvals_in = tree_map(lambda x: SymbolicTensor.like(get_symval(x)), args)
2743        static_args = tuple(static_args.items())
2744        if self.name is None:
2745            self.name = f"jit_{str(hash((self.f, symvals_in, static_args)))[-5:]}"
2746        program, consts, out_tree = make_program(self.f, *symvals_in, static_args=static_args, name=self.name)
2747        return program, consts, out_tree
2748        program, consts, out_tree = make_program(
2749            self.f,
2750            *symvals_in,
2751            static_args=tuple(static_args.items()),
2752            name=self.name,
2753        )
2754        return program, consts, out_tree
2755
2756    def __call__(self, *args, **static_args):
2757        program, consts, out_tree = self.get_program(*args, **static_args)
2758        args, in_tree = tree_flatten(args)
2759        # with Timing(f"JIT {self}"): outs = bind(backend.jit_op, *consts, *args, program=program)
2760        outs = bind(backend.jit_op, *consts, *args, program=program)
2761        return tree_unflatten(out_tree, outs)
2762
2763    def lower(self, *args, **static_args):
2764        program, consts, out_tree = self.get_program(*args, **static_args)
2765        args, in_tree = tree_flatten(args)
2766        hashed_program = Hashed(program)
2767        num_consts = program.num_consts
2768        consts, args = args[:num_consts], args[num_consts:]
2769        hashed_consts = tuple(map(Hashed, consts))
2770        jit_output = backend.jit_program(hashed_program, hashed_consts)
2771        return jit_output

2773    def export(self, args, output_path, export_params=True, input_names=None, output_names=None, **kwargs):
2774        if isinstance(args, Tensor):
2775            args, static_args = (args,), dict()
2776        elif not isinstance(args[-1], dict):
2777            assert all(isinstance(a, Tensor) for a in args)
2778            static_args = dict()
2779        else:
2780            args, static_args = args[:-1], args[-1]
2781        assert isinstance(args, (tuple, list)) and isinstance(static_args, dict)
2782        jit_output = self.lower(*args, **static_args)

527        params_strs = [k for k, v in sig.parameters.items() if v.kind == inspect.Parameter.KEYWORD_ONLY and k != "self"]

600    def args_fixer(self, x, w, **params):
601        if isinstance(x, UndefinedPrimal) or type(w) is UndefinedPrimal:
602            assert x.shape == w.shape
603            return (x, w), params
604
605        if type(x) in TraceTensor.PYTHON_TYPES:
606            x = backend.full(shape=(), fill_value=x, dtype=w.dtype)
607        elif type(w) in TraceTensor.PYTHON_TYPES:
608            w = backend.full(shape=(), fill_value=w, dtype=x.dtype)
609
610        shape_delta = x.ndim - w.ndim
611        if shape_delta > 0:
612            w = w.reshape((1,) * shape_delta + w.shape)
613        elif shape_delta < 0:
614            x = x.reshape((1,) * -shape_delta + x.shape)
615
616        shape_ret = tuple([max(x, w) for x, w in zip(x.shape, w.shape)])
617        if x.shape != shape_ret:
618            x = x.expand(shape_ret)
619        if w.shape != shape_ret:
620            w = w.expand(shape_ret)
621
622        if type(x) is Tensor and isinstance(w, TraceTensor):
623            x = w._trace.pure(x)
624        elif type(w) is Tensor and isinstance(x, TraceTensor):
625            w = x._trace.pure(w)
626        # TODO: https://jax.readthedocs.io/en/latest/type_promotion.html
627        if x.dtype != w.dtype:
628            # {int, bool} -> float
629            if dtypes.is_float(x.dtype) ^ dtypes.is_float(w.dtype):
630                if dtypes.is_float(w.dtype):
631                    x = x.cast(w.dtype)
632                elif dtypes.is_float(x.dtype):
633                    w = w.cast(x.dtype)
634            # bool -> int
635            elif dtypes.is_int(x.dtype) ^ dtypes.is_int(w.dtype):
636                if dtypes.is_int(w.dtype):
637                    x = x.cast(w.dtype)
638                elif dtypes.is_int(x.dtype):
639                    w = w.cast(x.dtype)
640            else:  # TODO: fine-grained type promotions
641                raise NotImplementedError("No other type promotion rules")
642
643        return (x, w), params

645    def vmap(self, dim_size, vals_in, dims_in, **params):
646        (x, w), (x_bdim, w_bdim) = vals_in, dims_in
647        if x_bdim != w_bdim:
648            if x_bdim is None:
649                x = VMapTrace.move_vmap_dim(x, dim_size, x_bdim, w_bdim)
650                x_bdim = w_bdim
651            else:
652                w = VMapTrace.move_vmap_dim(w, dim_size, w_bdim, x_bdim)
653        return [self(x, w, **params)], [x_bdim]

655    def typecheck(self, x: SymbolicTensor, y: SymbolicTensor, **params) -> List[SymbolicTensor]:
656        if not type(x) in (Tensor, SymbolicTensor) or not type(x) in (
657            Tensor,
658            SymbolicTensor,
659        ):
660            raise TypeError
661        symx = SymbolicTensor.like(x, dtype=dtypes.bool if self.boolean_output else x.dtype)
662        symy = SymbolicTensor.like(y, dtype=dtypes.bool if self.boolean_output else y.dtype)
663        if x.dtype != y.dtype:
664            raise TypeError(f"x.dtype ({x.dtype}) != y.dtype ({y.dtype})")
665        if symx == symy:
666            return [symx]
667        shape_delta = len(symx.shape) - len(symy.shape)
668        if shape_delta > 0:
669            symy = symy.like(shape=(1,) * shape_delta + symy.shape)
670        elif shape_delta < 0:
671            x = x.reshape((1,) * -shape_delta + symx.shape)
672            symx = symx.like(shape=(1,) * -shape_delta + symx.shape)
673        if symx == symy:
674            return [symx]
675        else:
676            shape_ret = tuple([max(x, w) for x, w in zip(symx.shape, symy.shape)])
677            if symx.shape != shape_ret:
678                symx = symx.like(shape=shape_ret)
679            if symy.shape != shape_ret:
680                symy = symx.like(shape=shape_ret)
681            if symx != symy:
682                raise TypeError(f"symx ({symx}) != symy ({symy})")
683            return [symx]

699class ReduceOperator(Operator):
700    def args_fixer(self, x, *, dim=None, keepdim=False):
701        if dim is None:
702            dim = tuple(range(x.ndim))
703        elif isinstance(dim, int):
704            dim = (dim,)
705        dim = tuple(a if a >= 0 else a + len(x.shape) for a in dim)
706        return (x,), dict(dim=dim, keepdim=keepdim)

708    def vmap(self, dim_size, vals_in, dims_in, *, dim, keepdim):
709        (x,), (x_bdim,) = vals_in, dims_in
710        dim = tuple(a + (x_bdim <= a) for a in dim)
711        out_bdim = x_bdim - sum(a < x_bdim for a in dim)
712        return [self(x, dim=dim, keepdim=keepdim)], [out_bdim]

def tree_transpose( outer_treedef: TreeDef, inner_treedef: TreeDef, tree_to_transpose: Any) -> Any: 
1934def tree_transpose(
1935    outer_treedef: TreeDef,
1936    inner_treedef: TreeDef,
1937    tree_to_transpose: Any,
1938) -> Any:
1939    flat, treedef = tree_flatten(tree_to_transpose)
1940    inner_size = inner_treedef.num_leaves
1941    outer_size = outer_treedef.num_leaves
1942    if treedef.num_leaves != (inner_size * outer_size):
1943        raise TypeError
1944    iter_flat = iter(flat)
1945    lol = [[next(iter_flat) for _ in range(inner_size)] for __ in range(outer_size)]
1946    permuted_lol = zip(*lol)
1947    subtrees = map(partial(tree_unflatten, outer_treedef), permuted_lol)
1948    return tree_unflatten(inner_treedef, subtrees)

def tree_map(f: Callable[..., Any], tree, *rest, out_leaf=False) -> Any: 
1966def tree_map(f: Callable[..., Any], tree, *rest, out_leaf=False) -> Any:
1967    leaves, treedef = tree_flatten(tree)
1968    if len(rest) == 0:
1969        out_tree_flat = tuple(f(leaf) for leaf in leaves)
1970        out_tree = tree_unflatten(treedef, out_tree_flat)
1971    else:
1972        all_leaves = [leaves]
1973        for t in rest:
1974            t_leaves, t_treedef = tree_flatten(t)
1975            assert t_treedef == treedef
1976            all_leaves += [t_leaves]

1980    ret = out_tree
1981    if out_leaf:
1982        ret = (ret, tree_flatten(out_tree_flat[0]))

2451
2452    tracer_to_var: Dict[int, Var] = {id(t): Var(SymbolicTensor.like(t.symval)) for t in tracers_in}
2453    constvar_to_val: Dict[int, Any] = {}
2454    constid_to_var: Dict[int, Var] = {}
2455    processed_instructions: Set[int] = set()

2458        if isinstance(t.draft, LambdaBindingDraft):
2459            assert id(t) in set(list_map(id, tracers_in))
2460        elif isinstance(t.draft, ConstDraft):
2461            val = t.draft.val
2462            var = constid_to_var.get(id(val))
2463            if var is None:
2464                symval = SymbolicTensor.like(get_symval(val))
2465                var = constid_to_var[id(val)] = Var(symval)
2466                constvar_to_val[var] = val
2467            tracer_to_var[id(t)] = var
2468        elif isinstance(t.draft, InstructionDraft):
2469            if id(t.draft) not in processed_instructions:
2470                instructions += [draft_to_instruction(tracer_to_var, t.draft)]
2471                processed_instructions.add(id(t.draft))
2472        else:
2473            raise TypeError(t.draft)
2474
2475    constvars, constvals = unzip2(constvar_to_val.items())
2476    in_binders = constvars + [tracer_to_var[id(t)] for t in tracers_in]
2477    # out_vars = [tracer_to_var[id(t)] for t in tracers_out if id(t) in tracer_to_var]
2478    out_vars = [tracer_to_var[id(t)] for t in tracers_out]

2480    typecheck_program(program)
2481    return program, constvals
def toposort(out_nodes: List[Any], parents: Callable[[Any], List[Any]]): 
2484def toposort(out_nodes: List[Any], parents: Callable[[Any], List[Any]]):
2485    def check_toposort(nodes: List[Any], parents: Callable[[Any], List[Any]]):
2486        seen = set()
2487        for node in nodes:
2488            assert all(id(parent) in seen for parent in parents(node))
2489            seen.add(id(node))
2490
2491    def remove_duplicates(lst):
2492        seen = set()
2493        return [x for x in lst if id(x) not in seen and not seen.add(id(x))]
2494
2495    if not out_nodes:
2496        return []
2497    out_nodes = remove_duplicates(out_nodes)
2498
2499    child_counts = {}
2500    stack = list(out_nodes)
2501    while stack:
2502        node = stack.pop()
2503        if id(node) in child_counts:
2504            child_counts[id(node)] += 1
2505        else:
2506            child_counts[id(node)] = 1
2507            stack.extend(parents(node))
2508    for node in out_nodes:
2509        child_counts[id(node)] -= 1
2510
2511    sorted_nodes = []
2512    childless_nodes = [node for node in out_nodes if not child_counts[id(node)]]
2513    while childless_nodes:
2514        node = childless_nodes.pop()
2515        sorted_nodes += [node]
2516        for parent in parents(node):
2517            if child_counts[id(parent)] == 1:
2518                childless_nodes += [parent]
2519            else:
2520                child_counts[id(parent)] -= 1
2521
2522    sorted_nodes = sorted_nodes[::-1]
2523    check_toposort(sorted_nodes, parents)
2524    return sorted_nodes

2591def backward_pass(program: Program, args: List[Any], cotangents: List[Any]) -> List[Any]:
2592    primal_env: Dict[Var, Any] = {}
2593    ct_env: Dict[Var, Any] = {}
2594
2595    def read_primal(x: Atom) -> Any:
2596        return primal_env.get(x, UndefinedPrimal(x.symval)) if type(x) is Var else x.val

2599        if type(val) is not UndefinedPrimal:

2602    def read_cotangent(v: Var) -> Any:
2603        return ct_env.pop(v, backend.zeros(v.symval.shape, v.symval.dtype))
2604
2605    def write_cotangent(x: Atom, ct: Any):
2606        if type(x) is Var and ct is not NullCotangent:

2615        cotangents_out = instruction.op.T(cotangents_in, *inp, **params)
2616        list_map(write_cotangent, instruction.inputs, cotangents_out)
